; federated-slices.form — cells share model SLICES over the mesh and merge them deterministically.
;
; THE NORTH STAR: a cell runs the best model it has locally; it shares small content-addressed model
; SLICES over the mesh; other cells ingest them through a trust-weighted, proven MERGE — and because the
; merge is a Form recipe, every cell merges to the SAME numbers (a deterministic federation, which a
; float-averaging PyTorch federation cannot promise). The model improves across the whole field without
; any cell ever degrading what it serves now.
;
; ── CURRENT FLOOR VS NORTH STAR (reviewed with Grok/Gemini/Claude, 2026-06-14) ──
;   CURRENT FLOOR: slice-merge.fk proves TIES sign-election plus trust-weighted FedAvg over integer
;     deltas; slice-update-roundtrip proves a model-delta update survives the mesh by re-addressing;
;     mesh-merge-converge proves merge order/path convergence; model-vitality.fk now adds explicit
;     delta-slice, eval-receipt, vitality, optimizer-state, and lineage rows for the model side of the
;     federation. model-data-sharing.fk now composes request-if-missing, re-address verification, apply,
;     substrate-source guard, and deterministic merge into one four-way slice-sharing receipt. These are
;     still small rows and proofs, not a real large-model chunk exchange or live mesh transport.
;     model-slice-chunk-range adds the bounded chunk-range policy: a slice can name contiguous tensor
;     chunk indexes under a chunk-set root and reject gaps, wrong tensors, and cache authority.
;     optimizer-delta-slice adds the matching optimizer-state delta receipt: valid optimizer cell ref,
;     before/after state ids, nonzero delta, chunk-range tie, and substrate-cell authority.
;     optimizer-step adds the exact integer SGD/momentum update math for the small vectors those slices
;     carry.
;     autodiff-gradient-cell adds the bounded scalar affine loss gradient rows that feed optimizer-step.
;     adam-step-cell adds bounded first/second moment update rows with an integer square-root denominator
;     and scalar autodiff gradient-vector handoff.
;     adam-bias-correction adds bounded fixed-point Adam bias-corrected moment and weight update rows.
;     Tensor-scale autodiff remains a model-kernel wall.
;   NORTH STAR: every federated update is a content-addressed slice over a known base merkle root:
;     (base-merkle, layer-ref, tensor-chunk-range, format-ref, quantization-context, delta-cell,
;     optimizer-state-delta, eval-receipt-ref, vitality-ref, n-samples, origin, ancestor-merge-refs).
;     Mergeability is a recipe returning (can-merge?, reason) from base equivalence, shape/format
;     compatibility, provenance compatibility, freshness, resonance, vitality, sovereignty, and trust.
;     Merge receipts record the elected sign, weight inputs, ancestor set, and output merkle root so the
;     mesh can avoid double counting and explain refusal without hidden policy.
;   GAP: chunk-range merkle proof over live payloads, chunk-aware live transport, tensor-autodiff, durable eval-receipt trust inputs,
;     merge-receipt ancestry, privacy/conflict policy, and body-readable vitality routing are not yet
;     real mesh payloads. The next proof should merge one tensor chunk-range slice, emit ancestry, and
;     update model vitality.
;
; ── THE SPLIT (shared slice vs cell-local), grounded in proven research ──
;   Three literatures converge on ONE shape: a stable shared core + small plastic shareable DELTAS.
;     - LoRA / adapters (ΔW = B·A): the shareable unit shrinks from d·k to r·(d+k) numbers; the base
;       never moves. The body already ships the forward: cell-numerics.form's adapter_forward(A,B,bias,x)
;       = matvec(B, matvec(A,x)) + bias (the "Adapter forward step", :59-76, :198-242).
;     - Task arithmetic (τ = θ_local − θ_base): a delta you carry, sum, scale. vector_sub/vector_add/
;       scalar_mul are on-main (cell-numerics.form:35-56) — compose (θ_base + λ·τ) and forget (−λ·τ).
;     - Complementary learning systems / CLS / EWC: the "short-term vs long-term" split is the
;       CONSOLIDATION POLICY, not the wire unit — fast = the cell's local adapter accumulating deltas;
;       long = the consolidated adapter it elects to SHARE once settled (active-inference.fk ai-settled?,
;       champion-challenger.fk cc-promote? are the gate).
;   WHY the shared slice is a LoRA/task-vector delta, not a whole short-term model: content-addressing
;   rewards small, stable, dedup-able payloads — identical adapter rows intern to one NodeID for free, a
;   re-derived adapter is recognized not re-sent (cell-sync.fk), and the (large, possibly private) base
;   stays cell-local (the sovereignty grain). A whole short-term model dedups poorly — every update is a
;   near-total retransmit, wasting the substrate's one native gift. Mergeability key: two cells can merge
;   only where their base NodeID matches (?equivalent / merkle-root is the check).
;
; ── THE UPDATE OVER THE MESH (a delta as a content-addressed cell) ──
;   FLOOR slice-update = (base-addr, layer-ref, format-ref, delta-cell, n-samples, origin). It rides the mesh
;   the body already has: cell-sync.fk offers merkle-root(delta-cell), a peer pulls only what it lacks
;   (cs-missing) and VERIFIES BY RE-ADDRESSING (cs-authentic?) — a forged delta fails its own address, so
;   the channel need not be trusted; mesh-relay.fk floods it (managed flooding, deduped on the content-
;   address, not an (src,seq) pair); friend-node.fk holds it for a sleeping peer; trust-decay.fk's
;   grace-band gives the per-peer trust weight. Gossip/decentralized-SGD IS managed-flooding + pairwise
;   merge — the body's mesh is gossip without ever calling it that.
;   NORTH-STAR slice-update extends the floor with tensor chunk ranges, optimizer-state deltas,
;   eval-receipt refs, vitality refs, and ancestor merge refs. The update carries enough resonance,
;   vitality, sovereignty, and trust evidence for the receiving body to plan: merge now, ask for more
;   samples, repair compatibility, or hold the slice without degrading the local champion.
;
; ── THE MERGE (proven strategy, as a Form recipe — slice-merge.fk, PROVEN three-way → 127) ──
;   trust-weighted FedAvg with TIES sign-election, division-free:
;     1. ELECT a sign per coordinate — the side with the larger summed weight wins (sm-elect). This is
;        confidence-weighted-vote.fk's integer weight-sum spine (cw-weight-for) specialized to a sign
;        condition; it stops the destructive interference plain averaging suffers when two cells learned
;        OPPOSING deltas.
;     2. AVERAGE only the sign-agreeing entries (disjoint merge): num = Σ wᵢ·τᵢ[j], den = Σ wᵢ over the
;        agreeing peers (sm-num / sm-den). The merged coordinate is the EXACT rational (num den) — the
;        divide is DEFERRED to apply-time, so the merge itself is integer-exact and identical on every
;        kernel. A gone peer (weight 0) cannot move it (proven: bit 64).
;   apply: θ_local = θ_base + (num/den)·… via cell-numerics vector_add/scalar_mul. The weight is
;   n-samples × trust-band(origin) — FedAvg's evidence count × trust-decay's freshness, kept integer.
;   (DARE drop-and-rescale and SLERP are later refinements; TIES+FedAvg is the proven floor.)
;   Structural deltas that are RECIPES (architecture edits, not weight nudges) use tree-diff.fk's
;   content-addressed diff/patch; named-layer conflicts use symbols-merge.fk's SYMBOLS-CONFLICT sentinel.
;
; ── THE MILESTONES ──
;   M0  merge two task-vector slices (TIES sign-election + trust-weighted FedAvg, order-stable, gone-peer
;       excluded) — SHIPPED: slice-merge.fk + tests/slice-merge-band.fk → 127, three-way.
;   M1  wrap the merged delta in a slice-update cell and round-trip it through cell-sync (offer → diff →
;       verify-by-re-address) — SHIPPED: slice-update-roundtrip.fk -> 127, and model-data-sharing.fk
;       composes the request/apply/source/merge receipt -> 4095 four-way.
;   M2  chunk-range slice policy — SHIPPED: model-slice-chunk-range -> 4095 four-way for contiguous
;       tensor chunk ranges under a chunk-set root; live mesh transport and payload merkle proof remain
;       next walls.
;   M3  optimizer-state delta slice — SHIPPED: optimizer-delta-slice -> 4095 four-way for optimizer cell
;       ref, before/after ids, nonzero delta, chunk-range tie, and substrate authority. Optimizer-step math
;       remains a model-kernel wall.
;   M4  optimizer-step math — SHIPPED: optimizer-step -> 4095 four-way for fixed-point SGD and momentum
;       receipts over small vectors.
;   M5  scalar affine gradient cells — SHIPPED: autodiff-gradient-cell -> 4095 four-way for prediction,
;       squared loss, dw/db gradient cells, and SGD handoff.
;   M6  bounded Adam moment cells — SHIPPED: adam-step-cell -> 4095 four-way for fixed-point first/second
;       moment updates, integer square-root denominator, and scalar autodiff gradient-vector handoff.
;   M7  Adam bias correction — SHIPPED: adam-bias-correction -> 4095 four-way for fixed-point corrected
;       moments and corrected weight updates. Tensor-scale autodiff remains later.
;   M8  three-cell mesh merge: two cells flood a slice-update via mesh-relay (content-address dedup), the
;       third merges both and applies it — assert mesh-merge NodeID == local-merge NodeID (gossip
;       convergence as a content-addressed proof).
;   M9  trust-weight it for real: w = n-samples × trust-decay grace-band; a silent peer's delta drops out.
;   M10 consolidation (short→long): gate "offer this adapter as shared" on ai-settled? + cc-promote?.
;   M11 apply on a real adapter_forward (cell-numerics) on tiny dims, output within format epsilon — the
;       merge demonstrably changes a model's behavior. Joins form-native-models.form M4 (the real block).
;
; KIN: form-native-models.form (the model-as-recipe + M1-M6; this is its distributed face) ·
;   cell-numerics.form (adapter_forward = LoRA; vector_add/sub/scalar_mul = task arithmetic) ·
;   confidence-weighted-vote.fk (the weight-sum spine slice-merge specializes) · cell-sync.fk +
;   mesh-relay.fk + friend-node.fk + trust-decay.fk + mesh-protocols-as-guide.form (the wire) ·
;   tree-diff.fk + symbols-merge.fk + merkle.fk (recipe-delta + conflict + the address) ·
;   active-inference.fk + champion-challenger.fk (settle/promote — the consolidation gate, AutoML M7).
